# Environment Variables Reference

## Local Development (Optional - defaults will work)

```bash
# Database - H2 (default) or MySQL
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:h2:mem:easyintern;MODE=MySQL;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DATABASE_TO_UPPER=false
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=sa
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=
SPRING_DATASOURCE_DRIVER_CLASS_NAME=org.h2.Driver

# JPA/Hibernate
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=update
SPRING_JPA_SHOW_SQL=true

# Security
SPRING_SECURITY_USER_NAME=admin
SPRING_SECURITY_USER_PASSWORD=admin

# Server
PORT=8080

# CORS
APP_CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:5175

# Frontend API URL (for frontend/.env or vite config)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
```

## PostgreSQL (Render Deployment)

```bash
# These are auto-set by Render from the database service:
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/database
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=auto-generated
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=auto-generated
SPRING_DATASOURCE_DRIVER_CLASS_NAME=org.postgresql.Driver
SPRING_JPA_DATABASE_PLATFORM=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=update
APP_CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://easyintern-frontend-v2.onrender.com
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://easyintern-api-v2.onrender.com
```

## MySQL (Self-Hosted)

```bash
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/easyintern
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=root
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=yourpassword
SPRING_DATASOURCE_DRIVER_CLASS_NAME=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=update
```

## AWS Deployment

```bash
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://your-rds-endpoint:3306/easyintern
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=admin
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=${DB_PASSWORD}  # Use AWS Secrets Manager
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=validate  # Don't auto-create on production
APP_CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-domain.com
```

## Azure Deployment

```bash
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://your-mysql-server.mysql.database.azure.com:3306/easyintern
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=admin@your-mysql-server
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=${DB_PASSWORD}  # Use Azure Key Vault
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=validate
```

## Docker Compose (Local Full Stack)

See `docker-compose.yml` for MySQL + backend + frontend setup:

```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

Then access:
- Frontend: http://localhost:5173
- Backend: http://localhost:8080
- Database: mysql://localhost:3306/easyintern

## Security Notes

⚠️ **NEVER commit sensitive values** to version control

For production deployments, use:
- **Render**: Environment variables in dashboard
- **AWS**: AWS Secrets Manager
- **Azure**: Azure Key Vault
- **Docker**: .env files (added to .gitignore)

Create `.env` file in project root (already in .gitignore):

```bash
# .env (local development only)
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=mypassword
SPRING_SECURITY_USER_PASSWORD=mypassword
```

Then reference in docker-compose or startup scripts.
